Below is a complete list of APIs you can test in Postman for your Express.js + Sequelize + MySQL backend.

I’ll include positive (valid) and negative (invalid) test cases so you can verify validation, errors, and edge cases.

1. Register User API

Endpoint

POST [http://localhost:5000/api/register](http://localhost:5000/api/register)

Body JSON

Positive Case

{
"name": "Riya Patel",
"email": "[riya@gmail.com](mailto:riya@gmail.com)",
"password": "123456",
"roleId": 1,
"companyId": 1,
"designationId": 1
}

Expected response

{
"message": "User registered successfully"
}

Negative Case 1 – Missing Name

{
"email": "[riya@gmail.com](mailto:riya@gmail.com)",
"password": "123456",
"roleId": 1,
"companyId": 1,
"designationId": 1
}

Expected

{
"error": "Name is required"
}

Negative Case 2 – Invalid Email

{
"name": "Riya",
"email": "riya",
"password": "123456",
"roleId": 1,
"companyId": 1,
"designationId": 1
}

Expected

{
"error": "Invalid email format"
}

Negative Case 3 – Email Already Exists

{
"name": "Riya Patel",
"email": "[riya@gmail.com](mailto:riya@gmail.com)",
"password": "123456",
"roleId": 1,
"companyId": 1,
"designationId": 1
}

Expected

{
"error": "Email already registered"
}

Negative Case 4 – Empty Password

{
"name": "Riya Patel",
"email": "[riya2@gmail.com](mailto:riya2@gmail.com)",
"password": "",
"roleId": 1,
"companyId": 1,
"designationId": 1
}

Expected

{
"error": "Password is required"
}

2. Login API

Endpoint

POST [http://localhost:5000/api/login](http://localhost:5000/api/login)

Positive Case

{
"email": "[riya@gmail.com](mailto:riya@gmail.com)",
"password": "123456"
}

Expected

{
"token": "JWT_TOKEN"
}

Negative Case 1 – Wrong Password

{
"email": "[riya@gmail.com](mailto:riya@gmail.com)",
"password": "wrongpass"
}

Expected

{
"error": "Invalid credentials"
}

Negative Case 2 – Email Not Found

{
"email": "[notfound@gmail.com](mailto:notfound@gmail.com)",
"password": "123456"
}

Expected

{
"error": "User not found"
}

3. Get Users (Pagination / Search / Sort / Filter)

Endpoint

GET [http://localhost:5000/api/users](http://localhost:5000/api/users)

Positive Case

Basic request

GET /api/users

Pagination

GET /api/users?page=1

Search

GET /api/users?search=riya

Sorting

GET /api/users?sortField=Email&sortOrder=ASC

Filtering

GET /api/users?role=1&company=2

Combined

GET /api/users?page=1&search=riya&sortField=Email&sortOrder=ASC&role=1&company=2

Negative Case – Invalid Sort Field

GET /api/users?sortField=password

Expected

Server should fallback to default sorting.

Negative Case – Invalid Page

GET /api/users?page=-1

Expected

Server should return page 1 or error.

